{% call components.section("Setting up") -%}

  <p>Our design kit is created in Adobe XD and includes various components and patterns for use in your designs. If the design kit is linked to your file, Adobe XD provides automatic updates of changes made to any of the components, so you’re always working with the latest designs. The design kit can also be viewed online if you need more design or development details about a component or pattern before you get started or while you’re working.</p>

  <div class="margin-top--4 inline-stack-mobile">
    <pfe-cta pfe-priority="secondary" style="margin-right:16px;">
      <a href="https://www.adobe.com/products/xd.html">Download Adobe XD</a>
    </pfe-cta>
    <pfe-cta>
      <a href="https://xd.adobe.com/spec/3e62e93c-8338-4f31-5040-3b81f0ed5c71-4853/grid">Browse the design kit online</a>
    </pfe-cta>
  </div>

{%- endcall %}

  <hr class="margin-top--10 margin-bottom--10">

{% call components.section("Start working") -%}

  <p>When you're ready to start working with the design system, follow these steps.</p>

  <div class="list-box">
    <div class="list-box--item">
      <div class="list-box--item-number">
        <span>1</span>
      </div>
      <div class="list-box--item-description">
        <h4>Get educated</h4>
        <p>Browse the website to familiarize yourself with our <a href="../foundations">Foundations</a> and <a href="../components">Components</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="list-box--item">
      <div class="list-box--item-number">
        <span>2</span>
      </div>
      <div class="list-box--item-description">
        <h4>Download the fonts</h4>
        <p>Download the <a href="https://github.com/RedHatOfficial/RedHatFont">Red Hat fonts</a> so typography and components will render correctly in your designs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="list-box--item">
      <div class="list-box--item-number">
        <span>3</span>
      </div>
      <div class="list-box--item-description">
      <pfe-modal id="connect-kit">
        <h2 slot="pfe-modal--header">Connect the design kit</h2>
        <p>In order to link the Adobe XD design kit to a new or existing file, follow these steps.</p>
        <h3>Show the Assets panel</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Press <em>Command + Shift + Y</em> (macOS) or <em>Control + Shift + Y</em> (Windows)</li>
          <li>Alternatively, click on the <em>View toolbar</em> menu and then <em>Assets</em></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Find the design kit cloud document</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Under the <em>Your Work</em> title, click on <em>Shared with You</em></li>
          <li>If you have multiple cloud files, the design kit features a thumbnail of a grid</li>
          <li>Click on the cloud file named <em>Red-Hat-Digital-Design-System-Kit.xdc</em></li>
          <li>The window will close and styles and components should be visible</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If you can't see the cloud file or can't link the design kit to a file, contact us.</p>
      </pfe-modal>

        <h4>Connect the design kit</h4>
        <p><a class="modal-launch" onclick="document.getElementById('connect-kit').open()">Link the Adobe XD design kit</a> to a new or existing file to get access to the components and patterns.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="list-box--item">
      <div class="list-box--item-number">
        <span>4</span>
      </div>
      <div class="list-box--item-description">
        <h4>Drag and drop</h4>
        <p>Start creating experiences by dragging and dropping components and patterns to the design canvas.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

